OL,3,C'Conspiracy of silence' over Katie
OL,4,CSimpson death
OL,6,FThe women's barristers told the judge
OL,7,Fthat their clients were all victims of
OL,8,FCreswell's abusive, violent and
OL,9,Fextremely controlling behaviour, and
OL,10,Fthey all had expressed genuine remorse
OL,11,Ffor their part in protecting him.
OL,13,FIt is accepted that none of the women
OL,14,Fbelieved they were involved in
OL,15,Fcovering up a murder, but believed
OL,16,Fthat they were assisting in covering
OL,17,Fup an assault on Katie.
